{"type": "article", "id": 46052, "title": "边刷边听音乐的牙刷，想哄小朋友好好刷牙｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2017-10-12T23:23:25Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 44663, "name": "Smithfly Designs"}, {"id": 44664, "name": "Clinic 212"}, {"id": 29315, "name": "BleepBleeps"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 14, "praise_count": 122, "image": "img/article/article_show/20171012173439N0F2KiyWO7bVmlPX.jpg", "contents": "<p nocleanhtml=\"true\">        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p4 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>Benjamin Brush by BleepBleeps</h3><p>还记得那个造型可爱的<a href=\"http://www.qdaily.com/articles/28599.html\">婴儿监视器</a>吗？它背后的英国育儿科技公司 <a href=\"http://bleepbleeps.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">BleepBleeps</a> 最近为那些因孩子不好好刷牙而困扰的家长支了新招——会放音乐的智能牙刷 Benjamin Brush。明亮的配色让 Benjamin 看起来就像是积木玩具，内置的扬声器会在刷牙时播放一首两分钟的曲目。配套的 App 既能购买新歌，也会将每次刷牙的时间转化成面积各异的圆圈，让一家人都能参与，旨在通过给刷牙加入仪式感和游戏感，让小朋友不再抗拒。它同时提供为更适合婴幼儿的圆形刷头以及普通的矩形刷头，让他们在长大后也能使用。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/bleepbleeps/benjamin-brush-the-smart-music-toothbrush-for-ever\" rel=\"nofollow\">众筹链接</a>，售价从 59 美元起。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173604sgC7aVeyIbk5DpoQ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.563235\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173604IlKbCw4a15nzrk0E.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667647\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173604RfA4rympadgbJKVq.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.561765\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Shoal Tent by Smithfly Designs</h3><p>水占据了地球 70% 的面积，我们能不能像在陆地上搭帐篷一样，搭一个水上帐篷享受户外的乐趣呢？由飞钓爱好者、设计师 Ethan Smith 成立于 2010 年的户外品牌 <a href=\"https://smithfly.myshopify.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Smithfly Designs</a> 通过新品 Shoal Tent 把这个想法转化成为现实。它号称是全球第一款充气式漂浮帐篷，不需要支撑杆，完全依赖气压抵御强风。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.smithfly.net/collections/watercraft/products/shoal-tent\" rel=\"nofollow\">购买链接</a>，售价为 1499 美元。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173617vsDIRH3O9fqgM6zG.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173617yqL35i7oKzJSYGwV.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>OkieDokie Super Simple Disaster Kit by Archie Archambault</h3><p>尽管红十字会以及美国联邦应急管理局（FEMA）都有给出“准备好应急包”这样的建议，美国设计师 Archie Archambault 发现，实际生活中人们往往会因为嫌麻烦或者不知道下手并没有做任何准备。为此，他根据 FEMA 给出的 72 小时应急包内容建议，开发了这款名为 <a href=\"https://www.okiedokie.online/\" rel=\"nofollow\">OkieDokie</a> 的应急包。简约统一的设计风格确保人们即便在惊慌失措的情况下，也能迅速找到物资。目前，这个应急包正在 Indiegogo 上开展<a href=\"https://www.indiegogo.com/projects/okiedokie-super-simple-disaster-kit-family-design--2#/\" rel=\"nofollow\">众筹</a>，售价从 199 美元起。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201710121736270urcsI8keWpEjOit.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666406\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173628YBzKkaISlTgpf3vW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.772840\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201710121736289VRwyxnu2fA4grIP.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.832099\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Time Tag Watch by Seohee Lee</h3><p>在某些不太好意思看手表的场合，我们该怎么确认时间？针对这一问题，韩国设计师 <a href=\"https://www.behance.net/seohee_lee\" rel=\"nofollow\">Seohee Lee</a> 受服饰标签的启发，带来了这款名为 Time Tag 的概念手表。表面由毛毡制成，时针和分针则以标签的形式表现，刻度也被设计在了表环边缘——只要用手轻轻一摸就能隐蔽地知道当前时间了。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173653cLYwS3pxrHU9d1l5.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.751667\" data-format=\"png\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173654jetNlTi39PCQOKYn.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.751667\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173653ebUc14WXR6o9OIj2.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.751667\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173653s8SfRlFMiuJqZQEO.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.751667\" data-format=\"png\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Toast Art by Eiko Mori</h3><p>你听说过“早吃好，午吃饱，晚吃少”的俗语吗？日本食物艺术家 <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/estyle1010/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Eiko Mori</a> 通过把吐司当画布的方式演绎了另一种意义上的“早吃好”。自今年初开始尝试这种可以吃的艺术以来，Mori 的创作已经相当娴熟：借助常见的牙签、汤勺和迷你管袋，她甚至可以制作出吐司上的“吐司”、“寿司”以及“天妇罗”等传统食物的图案。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173845whV1N8B96ZK5Iz3t.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.250667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"medium-insert-image-active\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"medium-insert-caption-placeholder\"></figcaption></figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173849P4n0lerZvx7ObiWm.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.250667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173846UVyBILEh1WCsf2bp.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.249333\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173847dmMpkyrQcfX0CWRZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.250667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Tiny Road Sign by Clinic 212</h3><p>说到人类和动物在城市和谐相处的有趣例子，你或许会想起在瑞典马尔默出现过的<a href=\"http://www.qdaily.com/articles/35857.html\">老鼠餐厅</a>和<a href=\"http://www.qdaily.com/articles/41101.html\">游乐园</a>。来自立陶宛的创意机构 <a href=\"http://www.clinic212.com/en/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Clinic 212</a> 也曾为此出谋划策，只不过他们选择从人类熟悉的路标入手，让更多人意识到自己身边其实还有这样一群邻居。在这个名为 Tiny Road Sign 的策划中，设计团队会根据当地的动物生态设计小一号的标识，甚至还有刺猬专用的斑马线。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173711FtQbixAOsPB6vV0I.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667045\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173711SedibDwhRZHc7Vqg.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667045\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173710eYLHjUERzD4vOM37.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667045\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20171012173711Bdqfj6ygrkbXIJP4.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667045\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div>"}